    "This process results in normal outputs from the LSTM model as normal values in time series while extreme output by transformers from all extreme values.",
    "The TXtreme framework uses a selective integration approach, routing sequences to either an LSTM for normal values or a transformer for extreme values based on a classifier's output.",
    "The final forecast is generated by merging outputs after denormalization and de-differencing.",
    "This hybrid approach uses specialized models for different data types, optimizing accuracy compared to traditional ensemble methods.",
    "Data segmentation and sampling for trainingThe TXtreme models utilize a sequence of L historical values to estimate the next H values, where L + H equals the total length of the analyzed time series segment."
